President Trump held a press conference in the East Room of the White House to announce new actions aimed at helping former inmates find employment and reintegrate into society. He emphasized the importance of providing second chances to individuals with criminal records and highlighted the success of his administration's efforts to create jobs and reduce unemployment rates for various minority groups. The President also acknowledged the passage of the FIRST STEP Act and praised the bipartisan support it received. Several individuals, including Kim Kardashian West, shared their personal stories and expressed their support for criminal justice reform. Additionally, the President announced partnerships with rideshare companies to provide transportation assistance for former inmates seeking employment.